Student Database Management System
COMP 3005 Assignment - A Python application for managing student records in PostgreSQL.

Video Demonstration (please forgive the sound quality it's not the best)
https://youtu.be/tyAOWMhQGVI


Prerequisites and dependencies 
Python
PostgreSQL 
pgAdmin 4 


Installation
Step 1. Install Python Library
pip install psycopg2-binary

Step 2. Set Up Database

Open pgAdmin or psql
Run Database_setup.sql to create the table
Run Database_insert.sql to add initial data

Step 3. Configure Connection (this is already in the code, but to mention it here, to make sure the steps are understood)
pythonconn = psycopg2.connect(
    host="localhost",
    database="DataBase",
    user="postgres",
    password="YOUR_PASSWORD",  # Change this
    port=5432                   # if you don't know your port number, you can use the Default port 5432
)

Running the Application
python test.py

----Now on to the Functions that I have created within the code----
check_connection()
Connects to the PostgreSQL database and checks for errors.

-----
getAllStudents(conn)
Retrieves and displays all student records from the students table.
Example:
getAllStudents(conn)

------
addStudent(first_name, last_name, email, enrollment_date, conn)
Adds a new student to the database with an auto-generated ID.
Example:
addStudent("John", "Doe", "john@example.com", "2025-09-01", conn)

------
updateStudentEmail(student_id, new_email, conn)
Updates the email address for a specific student.
Example:
updateStudentEmail(4, "newemail@example.com", conn)

-------
deleteStudent(student_id, conn)
Deletes a student record by student ID.
Example:
deleteStudent(4, conn)

Troubleshooting
Connection Error?

Check PostgreSQL is running
Verify your password and port number
Default port is 5432 

Module Not Found?
Make sure you do pip install psycopg2-binary to use the library commands


